The paper deals with properties of linear codes over finite fields, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The notion of pair weights and equiweight codes is related to error-correcting codes, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the MacWilliams extension theorem, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI).
